   Ad Notes. . . .
                                                                                                       

   STAFF MEETING: Banc One Corp. plans an unusual "staff
meeting," a 60-second spot to be aired on national TV on New
Year's morning. The Columbus, Ohio, bank holding company is
mailing memos to its 29,000 U.S. employees urging them to
tune in. During the ad, to be broadcast on CBS during the
Cotton Bowl Parade, Chairman and Chief Executive John B.
McCoy will discuss a new marketing effort. Details will come
Jan. 2 at the company's 747 offices. A Banc One spokesman
said the spot also may serve as a teaser for a related ad
campaign, scheduled to break at the end of January. Martin
Agency, Richmond, Va., created the ad.
                                                                                                       

   NEW ACCOUNT: The American Arbitration Association named
Alden Group, New York, to handle its new ad account. Billings
weren't disclosed. The New York-based association, which
mediates disputes, has done little advertising in the past.
